Super Eagles coach Jose Peseiro  said  he was thrilled with the hospitality accorded him at Ilorin when he went to watch Sunday’s Nigeria Professional Football League (NPFL) tie between Kwara United and Sunshine Stars. The newly engaged  national team manager is expected to integrate a sizeable number of players  from the domestic league  into the Super Eagles  as part  of his contract and  Ilorin was his first port of call  in what is expected  to be a regular visits to league centres across the country.   Sadio Mane in Munich ahead €41 million move from Liverpool     Nottingham Forest to pay record N8.7 billion for Awoniyi     WAFU B U17 Semis : Eaglets go for broke against Baby…   “It was a pleasure to meet and discuss Nigerian football with representatives from Kwara United and Sunshine Stars yesterday,” the 62-year-old former Venezuela coach noted via his verified Twitter handle @JosePeseiro. “Thank you all for your warm welcome and cordiality.” Meanwhile,  Kwara United striker  Alao Dabani said Peseiro presence in Ilorin on Sunday was a pleasant surprise, adding it would spur on  players in the local league to give  their best. “ It was good  to see him(Peseiro) ,” the 18-year-old striker  told Lagos based Sports Radio, Brila FM.“There is something he wanted to see  by coming to Ilorin; we  had  to show what we have  to do and  I think everybody did his best.”